+# Real-Time Collaborative Document Editor Implementation Plan
+
+> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.
+
+**Goal:** Build a collaborative real-time document editing server with REST API, WebSocket collaboration, OT-based conflict resolution, and SQLite persistence.
+
+**Architecture:** Express HTTP server with ws WebSocket server attached. Documents managed via REST endpoints. WebSocket connections per document for real-time collaboration. Operational Transform (OT) for conflict resolution with server as authority. SQLite via better-sqlite3 for persistence.
+
+**Tech Stack:** TypeScript, Express, ws, better-sqlite3, vitest for testing
+
+---
+
+### Task 1: Database Layer (`src/db.ts`)
+
+**Files:**
+- Create: `src/db.ts`
+
+**Implementation:**
+
+```typescript
+import Database from 'better-sqlite3';
+import { readFileSync } from 'fs';
+import { join, dirname } from 'path';
+import { fileURLToPath } from 'url';
+
+export interface Document {
+  id: string;
+  title: string;
+  content: string;
+  created_at: string;
+  updated_at: string;
+}
+
+export interface Version {
+  id: number;
+  document_id: string;
+  version: number;
+  content: string;
+  operation: string | null;
+  created_at: string;
+}
+
+export function createDatabase(dbPath?: string): Database.Database {
+  const db = new Database(dbPath || ':memory:');
+  db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');
+  db.pragma('foreign_keys = ON');
+
+  const schemaPath = join(dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url)), '..', 'schema.sql');
+  const schema = readFileSync(schemaPath, 'utf-8');
+  db.exec(schema);
+
+  return db;
+}
+```
+
+---
+
+### Task 2: OT Engine (`src/ot.ts`)
+
+**Files:**
+- Create: `src/ot.ts`
+
+**Implementation:**
+
+OT with insert and delete operations. Server transforms concurrent ops against each other.
+
+```typescript
+export type Operation =
+  | { type: 'insert'; position: number; text: string }
+  | { type: 'delete'; position: number; count: number };
+
+export function applyOperation(content: string, op: Operation): string {
+  if (op.type === 'insert') {
+    const pos = Math.min(Math.max(0, op.position), content.length);
+    return content.slice(0, pos) + op.text + content.slice(pos);
+  } else {
+    const pos = Math.min(Math.max(0, op.position), content.length);
+    const count = Math.min(op.count, content.length - pos);
+    return content.slice(0, pos) + content.slice(pos + count);
+  }
+}
+
+export function transformOperation(op: Operation, against: Operation): Operation {
+  // Transform op so it can be applied after against has been applied
+  if (op.type === 'insert' && against.type === 'insert') {
+    if (op.position <= against.position) return { ...op };
+    return { ...op, position: op.position + against.text.length };
+  }
+  if (op.type === 'insert' && against.type === 'delete') {
+    if (op.position <= against.position) return { ...op };
+    if (op.position >= against.position + against.count) {
+      return { ...op, position: op.position - against.count };
+    }
+    return { ...op, position: against.position };
+  }
+  if (op.type === 'delete' && against.type === 'insert') {
+    if (op.position >= against.position) {
+      return { ...op, position: op.position + against.text.length };
+    }
+    if (op.position + op.count <= against.position) return { ...op };
+    // delete range spans the insert point
+    return { ...op, count: op.count + against.text.length };
+  }
+  // delete vs delete
+  if (op.type === 'delete' && against.type === 'delete') {
+    if (op.position >= against.position + against.count) {
+      return { ...op, position: op.position - against.count };
+    }
+    if (op.position + op.count <= against.position) return { ...op };
+    // overlapping deletes
+    if (op.position >= against.position) {
+      const overlapEnd = Math.min(op.position + op.count, against.position + against.count);
+      const overlap = overlapEnd - op.position;
+      return {
+        type: 'delete',
+        position: against.position,
+        count: Math.max(0, op.count - overlap),
+      };
+    }
+    // op starts before against
+    const overlapStart = against.position;
+    const overlapEnd = Math.min(op.position + op.count, against.position + against.count);
+    const overlap = overlapEnd - overlapStart;
+    return {
+      type: 'delete',
+      position: op.position,
+      count: Math.max(0, op.count - overlap),
+    };
+  }
+  return { ...op };
+}
+
+export function validateOperation(op: unknown, contentLength: number): op is Operation {
+  if (!op || typeof op !== 'object') return false;
+  const o = op as Record<string, unknown>;
+  if (o.type === 'insert') {
+    return typeof o.position === 'number' && o.position >= 0 && typeof o.text === 'string' && o.text.length > 0;
+  }
+  if (o.type === 'delete') {
+    return typeof o.position === 'number' && o.position >= 0 && typeof o.count === 'number' && o.count > 0;
+  }
+  return false;
+}
+```
+
+---
+
+### Task 3: REST Routes (`src/routes.ts`)
+
+**Files:**
+- Create: `src/routes.ts`
+
+REST endpoints:
+- POST /documents - create
+- GET /documents - list
+- GET /documents/:id - get single
+- PUT /documents/:id - update
+- DELETE /documents/:id - delete
+- GET /documents/:id/versions - version history
+
+---
+
+### Task 4: WebSocket Handler (`src/ws.ts`)
+
+**Files:**
+- Create: `src/ws.ts`
+
+WebSocket protocol:
+- Client connects to `/ws/:documentId`
+- Server sends `{ type: 'sync', content, version }` on connect
+- Client sends `{ type: 'operation', operation, version }`
+- Server transforms against any concurrent ops, applies, broadcasts `{ type: 'operation', operation, version }` to other clients
+- Server sends `{ type: 'ack', version }` to sender
+- Error messages: `{ type: 'error', message }`
+
+---
+
+### Task 5: Server Entry Point (`src/server.ts`)
+
+**Files:**
+- Create: `src/server.ts`
+
+The `createApp` factory that wires everything together.
+
+---
+
+### Task 6: Tests
+
+**Files:**
+- Create: `src/__tests__/server.test.ts`
+
+Cover all rubric categories: REST CRUD, WebSocket lifecycle, single client editing, two-client convergence, stress test, error handling, persistence.
+
